HEADWORD: Stripling
<hw>Strip"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>strip</ets>; as if a small strip from the main stock or
steam.]</ety> <def>A youth in the state of adolescence, or just passing
from boyhood to manhood; a lad.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Inquire thou whose son the <qex>stripling</qex> is.</q> <rj><qau>1
Sam. xvii. 56.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stripper</ent>⟦br⟧
